            <h3><a name="fopb06jun"></a>Friends Of Purley Beeches working party, 6th June</h3>
            <p>Working party in Purley Beeches from 10 am to 2 pm. Tools, hot drinks and light refreshments will be provided. It is intended to continue clearing the area designated for replanting this autumn, along with further clearing of brambles and undergrowth. It is also planned that an area of thick hazel growth be coppiced, allowing re-growth of woodland flora. If you haven't attended a previous work party, please don't be put off. Come for as long or as little time that you can spare, but please wear suitable cloting, stout footwear and tough gardening clothes. For more information please contact Mac Court <%= mail_to "mac@skyy.me.uk" %>. Click the link to download a form to join the <%= link_to "Friends of Purley Beeches", "/resource/purley_beeches_enrol.pdf" %>.</p>
          </div><!-- col-md-10 -->
          <div class="col-md-2">
            <%= link_to image_tag("small-images/purley_beeches100.jpg", alt: "Purley Beeches logo"), "/resource/purley_beeches_enrol.pdf" %>
          </div><!-- col-md-2 -->
